    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="52"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Panaman Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Panama</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 1, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 21.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With profound sorrow have I heard of the demise
                    of the Hon. John Hay, Secretary of State, at Newbury, N. H., at 12.25 this
                    morning.</p>
                <p>The flag of the Republic of Panama will be kept at half-mast for three days as an
                    homage paid by my country to the eminent Secretary, whose death is looked upon
                    by it as a great national loss. The Republic of Panama sincerely joins in the
                    mourning of this nation for the everlasting departure of the distinguished
                    Secretary, John Hay.</p>
                <p>With sentiments of high regard, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. D. de Obaldía.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
